Job Description:
  The Trauma Data Analyst works closely with the Trauma Coordinator, Operations Director, and Medical Director to meet all the project coordination and data analysis needs, and is responsible for the coordination of data entry in the Ontario Trauma Registry. 
The Trauma Program Registry provides appropriate, accurate and timely analyses and interpretation of surgical and trauma care data to the Critical Care Services Ontario, Ministry of Health and Long Term Care (MOHLTC), Canadian Institute of Health Information (CIHI), physicians and health care professionals at Royal Victoria Regional Health Centre (RVH). In addition to this important role in patient care, the department also participates in the provision of data for medical, nursing and other health care provider education, performance, and quality improvement initiatives that may also include the Regional Trauma Network (RTN).


As a qualified candidate you will have the following job requirements:
Knowledge and Skills:

Completion of a Bachelor’s degree in Health Information Management, or other related field required, clinical background preferred;
Completion of an accredited postsecondary Health Information Management diploma an asset;
One (1-2) years related experience working in a health care environment preferred; 
Proficient in the use of Microsoft Office Products, e.g., Word, Excel, Access, Visio and PowerPoint, required;
Excellent analytical and problem solving skills with demonstrated ability to apply logical thinking to gathering and analyzing information;
Demonstrated suitable knowledge of medical terminology, pathology, anatomy, surgical procedures, and medical diagnostic & interventional terminology required.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills required;
Excellent interpersonal skills required;
Excellent coordinating and facilitating skills required;
Ability to implement advanced strategies for gathering, reviewing and analyzing data requirements;
Ability to prioritize requirements and apply best practices for effective communication and problem solving required.
Excellent communication skills with the ability to listen for clarity and meaning to ensure mutual understanding in a conversation required;
Demonstrated knowledge of Coding Standards and reporting required;
Demonstrated team player with the ability to interact with coworkers and clinicians in a positive manner required.
Proficiency with statistical analysis and applications.
Database administration and development skills.
Excellent time management skills.
Self-directed with a focus on accuracy.
Ability to prioritize and complete multiple projects simultaneously.



Accountability:

Accountability and reporting relationship to Decision Support with accountabilities to the Trauma Program leadership.
System-level accountability to Regional Trauma Network to meet data entry/analysis needs of the trauma program and related activities for the hospital.



Responsibilities:

Provide data analysis support for the trauma program to facilitate effective planning, decision-making, and project progress. 
Maintain responsibility for analyzing, interpreting, developing, and preparing timely/accurate ad hoc, monthly, quarterly, and yearly statistical data.
Ensure data quality and identify trends to highlight areas requiring further discussion. 
Assignment of other required codes and scales. These include but not limited to; CPT codes; ICD-10/external causes codes; Procedure codes; AIS 05 injury scaling 
Support collaboration with the RTN by providing ongoing analyses of hospital data for quality assurance and planning.
Provide ongoing analysis of regional trauma data to the hospital, CCSO, and Ontario Ministry of Health for purposes of quality assurance, planning, and funding as needed. 
Reviewing charts and determining proper ICD-10-CA/CCI and CPT codes when documentation is not clear
Responsible for attending program meetings and/or program related webinars.
Generation of reports related to performance improvement and patient safety initiatives and statistical tracking. 
Reporting data discrepancies to the Trauma Program Leadership team.
Develop program presentations and data related reports as required by the program.
Work collaboratively with Decision Support and Data Management to ensure data is up to date and accurate.
Maintains the integrity of highly confidential and sensitive information/communication.
Ability to Support the program’s strategic directions and priorities.
Performing statistical management, interpretation and other organizational responsibilities while acting as a primary contact for our Trauma Program interpreting information and ensuring the integrity and efficacy of surgical and trauma data, while also informing corporate and program decision initiatives; 
Communicating effectively with hospital wide departments, building a relationship to ensure corporate and program clinical objectives are met;
Accurately code and abstract clinical and administrative data, using standardized national and international classification systems and abstracting software, from patient health records in accordance with international (ACS), national (CIHI), and provincial (MOHLTC) standards. The coding specialist ensures coding/data collection accurately reflects chart documentation and participates in regular quality assurance activities.
Develops, prepares and submits CIHI Ontario Trauma Registry (OTR), Decision Support, and/or Critical Care Services Ontario (CCSO) clinical process and outcome indicator data, in a timely manner, acting as a key contact for providing assistance with data clarity and interpretation;
Performs clinical data analyses for trauma and surgical care areas responding to data queries to support effective and efficient management strategies, identifying areas where our programs and clinical care are exemplary, as expected and requiring improvement;
Reviews and interprets patient information, and applies relevant coding classifications including ICD10CA, CCI, AAAM AIS and/or CPT methodology for capturing all diagnoses, interventions and procedures following Canadian and International Coding Standards;
Access patient’s record electronically via Meditech, and external applications such as Med 2020, EMS call record thoroughly analyzing all documentation and ensuring registration data is consistent with clinical documentation;
Applies coding skills to code procedures, diagnosis and/or injuries using multiple software applications including WinRec (Med2020);
Performs monthly QA of coded data correcting issues provided to them by Manager or Decision Support Services;
Performs analysis of charts to ensure completion;
Participates in data quality audits to ensure correct assignment of codes and optimization data capture for hospital (Trauma base funding) and others as required; 
Monthly Data quality audits and ISS reconciliation with Decision Support; 
Provides support for research and quality improvement projects by identifying, monitoring and tracking clinical data;



Education:

Completion of an undergraduate degree in Health Information Management, or other related field required, clinical background preferred; or a minimum of 5 years equivalent experience required.
Certification as a Health information specialist is an asset.
One (1-2) years experience working in a health care environment preferred; 
Minimum of 2 years related experience in the field.



Experience:

Experienced in Health Information Management.
Analytical, data interpretation and facilitation skills.
Knowledge of Coding Standards and reporting.
Advanced Excel expertise including functions, pivot tables, text to columns, and other commonly used data cleansing techniques.
Microsoft Office Suite.
Healthcare Reporting Tools.
Strong ability to present data in an organized and professional manner through various means.
Experience in work related to data quality is required.
Knowledge of medical terminology required.

Company Description
  Assent is the supply chain sustainability management solution for the world’s most responsible, sustainability-focused complex manufacturers. The #1 business risk for complex manufacturers is hidden. Most supply chains were never built with sustainability in mind, and most manufacturers do not have deep visibility into their supply chain risks while outsourcing the majority of their production. Shaped by regulatory experts, customers and suppliers, Assent is the foundation manufacturers need for cross-enterprise sustainability. At Assent, your work will help bring transparency, sustainability, and fairness to the global community.
 We’re one of the fastest-growing technology companies - from $5 million to $50 million ARR in under five years! As the global leader in supply chain data management, we provide transparency into the supply chains of some of the world's largest and most successful companies, including 75 percent of Fortune 500 companies. In our most recent funding round, we raised $350 Million USD in funding led by Vista Equity Partners. This funding will allow us to continue to scale with purpose, and add exceptional talent to our already remarkable team.



 Job Description
  Reporting to the Senior Director, Product Marketing, we will depend on you to take ownership of our pricing strategy at Assent. You will conduct market research to determine the correct market price for Assent’s solutions. The ideal candidate will bring a value-based, data-driven approach to develop, contextualize and adapt a pricing strategy. We’re growing fast and this is a great opportunity to make an impact, both at Assent and with the thousands of suppliers and customers that rely on us to help keep their products safe, sustainable and compliant.

 Be the expert on pricing, packaging and bundling for Assent’s solution suite;
 Collaborate with internal teams and external agencies to develop and adapt our pricing strategy including a full portfolio pricing review;
 Support the revenue operations team with existing pricing models help with the development and evaluation of alternative pricing structures;
 Partner with Revenue Operations to design and implement annual price changes;
 Sets price points to maximize TAM and aligns pricing structures to customer usage and value growth;
 Apply marketing strategy and pricing fundamentals to set price for new offerings;
 Provide detailed insight into KPIs for the purposes of revenue tracking, future planning, and strategic decision making;
 Support monitoring competitors including pricing trends, gaps and advantages.




 Qualifications

 Level of education, training and experience equivalent to a degree in market research, business administration; finance, or related field;
 7+ years related experience in Corporate strategy, Portfolio pricing, Market research/analysis, Product Management, Product Marketing, Consulting, Sales Operations;
 Strong analytical skills with experience gathering and defining requirements, analyzing data, and delivering detailed conclusions;
 Excellent written, verbal, and visual presentation communication skills;

 Additional Information
  At Assent, we are uniquely positioned to make meaningful, impactful changes in the world around us. If you believe in doing work that matters, we want you to join our team.
 Life at Assent

 Wellness: We believe that you and your family’s well being is important. As a result, we offer vacation time that increases with tenure, comprehensive benefits packages (details vary by country), life leave days and more.
 Financial Benefits: It’s not all about the money – well, it’s a little about the money. We understand that financial health is important and we offer a competitive base salary, a corporate bonus program, retirement savings options and more.
 Life at Assent: There is purpose beyond your work. We provide our team members with volunteer days, flexible work options and opportunities to get involved in corporate giving initiatives.
 Lifelong Learning: At Assent, curiosity is not only valued but encouraged. You will receive professional development days that are available to you the day you start.
 Work The Way That Works for You: Your work and life should be balanced in a way that is purposeful for you. We offer flexible working environments for our team. Choose a space that meets your unique needs.


 Work the way that works for you. Your work and life should be balanced in a way that is purposeful for you. At Assent, we offer flexible working environments for our team. Choose a space that meets your unique needs.
 At Assent, we are committed to growing and sustaining an environment where our team members feel included, valued, and heard. Our diversity and equal opportunity practices are guided and championed by our Diversity and Inclusion Working Group and our Employee Resource Groups (ERGs).
 Our commitment to diversity, equity and inclusion includes recruiting and retaining team members from diverse backgrounds and experiences, and fostering a culture of belonging where all team members are included, treated with dignity and respect, promoted on their merits, and placed in positions to contribute to business success.
